The '''Tibetan Language Institute''' is a private, non-profit educational organization located in [[Hamilton, Montana]]. Its mission is to present classes, seminars, workshops, and public lectures on Tibetan [[Tibetic languages|language]], [[Tibetan literature|literature]], and philosophy for the purpose of preserving [[Tibetan culture]] and enriching one's study of the [[Dharma (Buddhism)|Dharma]].<ref>[http://www.omniglot.com/writing/tibetan.htm Tibetan alphabet, pronunciation and language<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.nonprofitlist.org/cgi-bin/id/nonprofit.cgi?nonprofit=54340 Tibetan Language Institute | Tibetan Language Institute Hamilton Montana | Non Profit Organization<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.wiserearth.org/organization/view/320a1b1a1044950a8de1511e6bf2c947 Organization: Tibetan Language Institute<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> The main program of study is a series of classes in the Tibetan lanaguage (available via distance learning or through private tutoring in person).<ref>[http://www.learntibetan.net/resources/institutes.htm Tibetan Language Institutes<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
